            fork_exec(child, argv[1]);

            // Terminate the child process
            kill(child, SIGTERM); // Send a SIGTERM signal to the child process

            // Continue running the parent process
            return 0;
        }
        ```

Remember to use these methods judiciously, as terminating a program abruptly can lead to data corruption or other issues.  |
